===Etymology===
From Chinese [[еҸӨзҗҙ]] (gЗ”qГӯn), from [[еҸӨ]] вҖҳancientвҖҷ + [[зҗҙ]] вҖҳstringed instrumentвҖҷ.

===Noun===
{{en-noun|guqin}}

# {{musici}} A plucked seven-string Chinese [[musical instrument]] of the [[zither]] family 
#:*'''1982''': Among those who will be making the Otter valley resound to the strains of the ''guzheng'' and ''erhu'' is Wu Wenguang, who plays a piece of music 1,800 years old on the '''''guqin''''', an instrument known to have existed 3,000 years ago вҖ” ''The Times'', 25 May 1982, p.10 col. C

